Rating: 4
This egg salad is delicious. My husband doesn't even like egg salad and he ate this for dinner and took it for lunch the next day. The sweet of the pickles with the sharper onion flavors and the tarragon work great together. We are not dijon mustard fans so I used regular and it was great. Highly recommended, quick, easy, and vegetarian! Served it on pretzel batards with just a slice of romaine. A great summer sandwich with corn on the cob on the side and heirloom tomatoes!

